- The `binarySearch` function takes an array and a target value as input.
- It initializes `left` and `right` pointers to the start and end of the array, respectively.
- It repeatedly calculates the middle index (`mid`) and compares the value at `mid` with the target.
- Depending on whether the middle value is less than or greater than the target, it adjusts the `left` or `right` pointer to narrow the search range.
